[[File:Eyach1.jpg|thumb|Southern pylon of the Eyachtal Span]]
The '''Eyachtal Span''' is the crossing of the [[Eyach (Enz)|Eyach]] valley with a [[Electric power transmission|110 kV line]] in [[Neuenbürg]] and [[Höfen an der Enz]] in the [[Black Forest]] in [[Germany]]. The Eyachtal Span was built in 1992. With a [[span (architecture)|span]] of 1444 metres, it is the greatest span of a power line in Germany. The [[Electricity pylon|pylon]]s on which the Eyach Span is fixed are 70 metres high and located on [[Heuberg (Buchenbach)|Heuberg]] and [[Eiberg]].

