'''Hugo Jabini''' is a [[Saramaka]]n from the Laduani village by the [[Suriname River]]. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2009, jointly with [[Wanze Eduards]], for their efforts of protecting their traditional land and [[tropical rainforest]]s against industrial logging, supported by the [[Inter-American Commission on Human Rights]] and the [[Inter-American Court]].<ref name=goldman>{{cite web |url=http://goldmanprize.org/2009/southcentralamerica |title=Wanze Eduards and S. Hugo Jabini. Suriname Forests |publisher=Goldman Environmental Prize |accessdate=22 November 2010}}</ref> 

