'''Jack's Magazine''' (also known as the Saltwater River [[gunpowder magazine|Gunpowder Magazine]]) is located on the [[Maribyrnong River]] at [[Maribyrnong, Victoria]]. The complex opened in 1878, to provide safe storage for bonded gunpowder and explosives imported into the colony of Victoria. The twin [[bluestone]] vaulted buildings are concealed behind high earth mound blast walls, and a tall bluestone wall, with a canal connecting it to the river. It was designed by government architect, [[William Wilkinson Wardell|William Wardell]], Inspector General, Public Works Department and built by contractor [[George Cornwell]].<ref>J W Moore, 'The Saltwater River Powder Magazine (now known as Jack's Magazine)', 1969 (Notes Distributed By The Ammunition Factory);  Sir John K Jensen, ''Defence Production In Australia' to 1941', 1964 (Copy Held  By The Ammunition Factory)</ref>

[[File:JacksMagazine.jpg|thumb]]

It is registered by the National Trust,<ref>[http://vhd.heritage.vic.gov.au/search/nattrust_result_detail/66087 Jack's Magazine (Ammunition Factory)]</ref> and listed on the Victorian Heritage Register.<ref>{{cite VHD|3770|Jack's Magazine|hr=1154|ho=45}}</ref> The associated Footscray Ammunition Factory was mostly demolished and redeveloped for the [[Delfin Lend Lease]] Corporation's Edgewater estate.<ref>[http://www.edgewater.com.au/ Edgewater - A Delfin Lend Lease Project]</ref> Jack's Magazine was proposed to be redeveloped for a commercial use, but following several calls for expressions of interests it was decided that public ownership was the only practical management for the historic site.<ref>[http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/bluestone-time-capsule-ready-to-enter-a-new-century-20100308-psqv.html#ixzz1XLLO8gXe Bluestone time capsule ready to enter a new century]</ref> Jack's Magazine is now managed by [http://www.workingheritage.com.au/ Working Heritage] – a committee appointed by the Victorian Government to manage heritage properties on Crown Land.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Jack's Magazine: Mining ideas for forgotten explosives store on Maribyrnong's banks|url = http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/new-use-sought-for-forgotten-explosives-store-on-the-banks-of-the-maribyrnong-20150909-gjip5n.html|newspaper = The Age|date = 2015-09-09|access-date = 2015-10-21|first = Clay|last = Lucas}}</ref>

