'''Nuclear Electric Insurance Limited''' ('''NEIL''') is a [[mutual insurance]] company which insures all [[nuclear power plant]]s in the United States as well as some facilities internationally. The company is based in [[Wilmington, Delaware]], and is registered in [[Bermuda]].<ref name="neilhistory"/>
It was founded in 1980 in response to the 1979 [[Three Mile Island accident]].<ref name="tbt20121230">{{cite web |url= http://www.tampabay.com/news/business/energy/article1268290.ece |work= [[Tampa Bay Times]] |title= Utilities nationwide could share the financial pain of the idled Crystal River nuclear plant |first1= Ivan |last1= Penn |date=December 30, 2012 |accessdate= December 30, 2012}}</ref> In 1997 NEIL merged with Nuclear Mutual Limited, of Bermuda.<ref name="neilhistory">{{cite web |url= http://www.nmlneil.com/about-us/company-information/neil-history.aspx |title= NEIL History |publisher= Nuclear Electric Insurance Limited |accessdate= December 30, 2012}}</ref>
