{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}} {{Infobox power station | name = Reckahn Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|52|20|N|12|33|E|region:DE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = <ref>{{cite web|title=Reckahn Solar Park in global mapping of solar power station site footprints|url=http://www.wiki-solar.org/map/sites/index.html?Reckahn?u?15?52.3456?12.5619?|publisher=Wiki-Solar|accessdate=5 March 2015}}</ref> | country = Germany | location = Reckahn | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = 2010, 2011 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | solar_site_area = {{convert|85|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}} [http://www.wiki-solar.org/map/sites/index.html?Reckahn?Pk60017?16?52.3456,12.5619 Site plan] | ps_electrical_capacity = 37.7 [[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }}
'''Reckahn Solar Park''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in Reckahn, Southwest of [[Berlin]], Germany. It has a [[Nameplate capacity|capacity]] of 37.7 [[megawatt]] (MW) and was constructed in three phases.<ref name="pvresources.com">[http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx Large-Scale Photovoltaic Power Plants] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101115142/http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx |date=1 January 2016 }}</ref><ref name="pvresources.com"/><ref>[http://www.belectric.com/en/solar-power-plants/projects/ Projects]</ref><ref>[http://www.lbbw.de/imperia/md/content/lbbwde/presse/de/2010/Reckahn-Rentweinsdorf.pdf LBBW finanziert Photovoltaikparks in Bayern und Brandenburg]</ref> ''Reckahn I'' was 22.661 MW covering {{convert|56|ha|acre}} and was built by Beck Energy GmbH (Belectric) using 292,000 First Solar thin-film [[Cadmium telluride photovoltaics|CdTe-panels]], and was expected to produce about 22 [[GWh|gigawatt-hours]] per year.<ref>[http://www.bayernlb.de/internet/media/internet_4/en_1/downloads_14/0100_corporatecenter_10/1323presse_politik_5/pressemeldungen_3/2010_25/08august_22/11082010-Projektfinanzierung-Reckahn-eng.pdf BayernLB provides financing for the Reckahn I solar power plant in Brandenburg]</ref> ''Reckahn II'' added 13.3 MW, using 172,000 modules on a {{convert|35|ha|acre}} site.<ref name="LBBW-press-14274">LBBW Landesbank Baden-Württemberg, [http://www.lbbw.de/de/presse/presseinformationen/presse_detail_14274.jsp LBBW finanziert Photovoltaikparks in Bayern und Brandenburg], 15 September 2010</ref> ''Reckahn III'', completed in 2011, added 1.8 MW, bringing the total to 37.7 MW. The [[Feed-in tariffs in Germany|FIT]] is 21.1 Euro cents per [[kilowatt-hour]].<ref>[http://basisplusweb.bit-ag.com/DDT4-8MWD-EUPF-MHM9/de/beteiligung/9E20308D,BB37,4CFC,AB0E,347AB208C155/Projektdaten.htm Solar-Deutschlandportfolio 4]</ref>
